metatags.twitter:description: Paul Zhang is a seasoned technology leader and co-founder at Avant, where he plays a pivotal role in shaping the future of online financial services. With a strong technical background in software development and a focus on web applications, he has led teams in creating innovative lending platforms. Paul has a rich history of involvement in startups, including his tenure as a technical founder at Debteye Inc, which was part of Y Combinator. His experience spans key roles such as Chief Information Officer and Chief Technology Officer, showcasing his adaptability and leadership in the fast-paced fintech industry. A board member at the University of Illinois Grainger College of Engineering, he is passionate about mentoring the next generation of engineers. Pauls diverse skill set includes expertise in Ruby on Rails, PostgreSQL, and front-end technologies, making him a valuable asset in any tech-driven organization.
